# How to Create and Delete a MySQL Database

# To access the MySQL shell:

$ mysql -u root -p

# To view what databases are available (none at the moment, do the following commands):

$ SHOW DATABASES;

+--------------------+
| Database           |
+--------------------+
| information_schema |
| TestDB             |
| mysql              |
| performance_schema |
+--------------------+

$ CREATE DATABASE TestDB;

# To Delete a database do:

$ DROP DATABASE TestDB;

# To Access the new Database do:

$ USE TestDB;

# To view the tables of this new DB:

$ SHOW TABLES;

# Next you will need to create tables in your Database.
